SM.POP.NETM-migration.def: Net migration is the number of immigrants minus the number of emigrants, including citizens and noncitizens, for the five-year period.
SM.POP.NETM-migration.name: Net migration
SM.POP.NETM-migration.source: United Nations Population Division. World Population Prospects: 2019 Revision.

SM.POP.REFG-migration.def: Refugees are people who are recognized as refugees under the 1951 Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees or its 1967 Protocol, the 1969 Organization of African Unity Convention Governing the Specific Aspects of Refugee Problems in Africa, people recognized as refugees in accordance with the UNHCR statute, people granted refugee-like humanitarian status, and people provided temporary protection. Asylum seekers -- people who have applied for asylum or refugee status and who have not yet received a decision or who are registered as asylum seekers--are excluded. Palestinian refugees are people (and their descendants) whose residence was Palestine between June 1946 and May 1948 and who lost their homes and means of livelihood as a result of the 1948 Arab-Israeli conflict. Country of asylum is the country where an asylum claim was filed and granted.
SM.POP.REFG-migration.name: Refugee population by country or territory of asylum
SM.POP.REFG-migration.source: United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) and UNRWA through UNHCR's Refugee Data Finder at https://www.unhcr.org/refugee-statistics/.

SM.POP.REFG.OR-migration.def: Refugees are people who are recognized as refugees under the 1951 Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees or its 1967 Protocol, the 1969 Organization of African Unity Convention Governing the Specific Aspects of Refugee Problems in Africa, people recognized as refugees in accordance with the UNHCR statute, people granted refugee-like humanitarian status, and people provided temporary protection. Asylum seekers--people who have applied for asylum or refugee status and who have not yet received a decision or who are registered as asylum seekers--are excluded. Palestinian refugees are people (and their descendants) whose residence was Palestine between June 1946 and May 1948 and who lost their homes and means of livelihood as a result of the 1948 Arab-Israeli conflict. Country of origin generally refers to the nationality or country of citizenship of a claimant.
SM.POP.REFG.OR-migration.name: Refugee population by country or territory of origin
SM.POP.REFG.OR-migration.source: United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), Refugee Data Finder at https://www.unhcr.org/refugee-statistics/.

SM.POP.TOTL-migration.def: International migrant stock is the number of people born in a country other than that in which they live, including refugees.
SM.POP.TOTL-migration.name: International migrant stock
SM.POP.TOTL-migration.source: United Nations Population Division, Trends in Total Migrant Stock: 2012 Revision.
